{
  "text": "Waf1/CIP1 -mediated cell cycle arrest, further promoting commitment to keratinocyte differentiation [CITATION_1] . Our results suggest that elevated p300 expression in differentiating cells could also induce K111 acetylation, thereby stimulating E2-dependent transcription. The resulting increase in early gene protein levels, specifically E1, could induce viral DNA amplification, linking it to the differentiated status of the infected cell. The role of K111 acetylation by p300 in regulation of the viral replicative program is currently under active investigation.",
